        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued July 15 at 5:01PM EDT until July 15 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 500 PM EDT, a severe thunderstorm was located 7 miles north of
McLeansville, or 9 miles south of Reidsville, moving northeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, McLeansville, Gibsonville, Haw River State Park, Lake
Townsend Marina, Lake Townsend, and Monticello.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.

Continuous cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Move indoors immediately. Remember, if you can hear thunder, you are
close enough to be struck by lightning.</instruction>
